### 0.3 Bibliography Gap Summary

The project bibliography exists only in `/mnt/project/bibliography-v8.md` (274 lines, ~112 entries). It is **not committed to GitHub**, not linked from the guidebook body (which has an empty placeholder), and does not reflect sources accumulated since March 2026. The BPC has 30 DOI references and cites sources across 21 Key Sources sections that have no corresponding bibliography entries.

**Missing from bibliography (confirmed):**
- All sources added in BPC entries since 2026-03-17 (~60+ sources)
- All BPC-8 additions specified in Workplan_BPC_Corrections (16 new + 4 updates)
- Cross-reference bibliography compendium Category A additions (12 high-value confirmed sources including Keall 2015 Lancet Tier 1 RCT)
- BPC Key Sources sections from 21 full-schema slugs
- Recent standards: NEN 9120:2025; NCC 2022; ABCB Livable Housing v1.3; Habinteg 2024

### 0.4 Skill Ecosystem — Deployment Summary

Skills execute from `/mnt/project/` (canonical execution source per project-standards Rule). GitHub `skills/` directory is inventory-only — **never read at runtime**. All 26 registered skills are in `/mnt/project/`. Three skills relevant to this workplan are defined inline in Project Instructions only (no `/mnt/project/` file): `research-log-manager`, `workplan-orchestrator`, `session-consolidator`.

`keyword-lookup` is a registered skill (`/mnt/project/keyword-lookup_SKILL.md`) that must be called before any `multilingual-research` run (complements the Keyword Compendium `view` step). This step is distinct from and supplementary to the Compendium view.

`citation-miner` is listed as "to build (P2)" — does not yet exist. Citation mining is performed inline within `multilingual-research` until built.

`vol2-item-formatter` is in the orchestrator skill registry and is the terminal step in the Item Specification workflow. Confirm the skill file is present in `/mnt/project/` before WS-3 execution begins.

