## Part 2 — Critical Path and Work Stream Architecture

```
PHASE 0 (Parallel — no dependencies):
  WS-4  Gap register hygiene
  WS-5  BPC corrections (Sessions 1–2 + BPC-7 re-research)
  WS-6  Infrastructure + bibliography bootstrap
  BPC-1 Safety-critical temperature correction (IMMEDIATE)

PHASE 1 (Sequential — WS-1 gates everything below):
  WS-1  Pre-session: fix-linebreaks on source file
  WS-1A CO-0001 execution (12 passes, find-and-replace Stages 0–6)
  WS-1B Structural verification (haiku-chunker → cross-reference-resolver → audit)

PHASE 2 (After Phase 1):
  WS-2  Body corrections (Sessions A–D)
  BPC-3 through BPC-6 (after Decisions A+B confirmed, BPC-1+2 complete)

PHASE 3 (After Phase 2):
  WS-3  Population coverage additions (DBL, IntD, DEAF, new items)
  WS-6B Bibliography compilation (after BPC-8)

PHASE 4 (All phases complete):
  WS-7  Final assembly, audit, version increment, session close
```

