## Part 3 — Work Stream 1: Structural Execution (CO-0001)

### WS-1 Pre-session — DOCX Conversion Prep (mandatory; PI Rule 14)

**Rule:** `fix-linebreaks` before any analysis or substitution skill on a DOCX-converted file.  
**Risk:** CO-0001 has 12 find-and-replace passes. Running them against hard-wrapped Part 8 text (~5,000 lines, ~8–10 words per line) will produce systematic missed instances and false positives in item specifications. This is not recoverable after execution.

1. Run `fix-linebreaks` on `Guidebook_for_Accessible_Design_8v09_2026-03-18-12-50.md` (full file, 11,763 lines). Idempotent — safe to run on clean sections.
2. Spot-check: item A-01 description. If still one sentence per line → `fix-linebreaks` did not execute. Do not proceed.
3. Backslash escape artifacts (`\\'s`, `\\\[`, `\\\\`) are a separate artifact class. After `fix-linebreaks`, run a targeted `find-and-replace` Stage 1 discovery pass for `\\\\` and `\\\[`. Classify and execute if present.
4. Output: clean `.md` base file for all subsequent operations.

### WS-1 Session A — CO-0001 Execution

**Pre-flight (PI Rule 13 mandatory — no fast-track exception):**  
Verify on GitHub:
- `references/toc.md` reflects Parts 1–13 structure (CO-0001 applied to ToC ✓)
- CO-0001 sign-off checklist: `toc.md updated: ✓` and `Change Order committed: ✓`
- No structural decisions made since CO-0001 that require a CO-0002 first

`find-and-replace` — all six stages (0–6) per pass. Stages 0–6 are: spec confirmation, instance discovery (Haiku), classification (Sonnet), downstream impact, execution, validation, gap register write.

| Pass | CO ref | Escalation notes |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | CO-0001-A: Volume 1/2/3 → I/II/III | >50 instances — confirm bulk at Stage 0 |
| 2 | CO-0001-B: Part labels + codes Vol I (Parts 1–3) | |
| 3 | CO-0001-C: Delete Part IV block | REMOVE — redirect all cross-refs to Part 7 §7.x before deleting content |
| 4 | CO-0001-D: Part labels + codes Vol II (Parts 4–10); V2-P4- → V2-P8- | CODE instances: pause at Stage 2; `volii-validator` on V2-P4- instances before replacing |
| 5 | CO-0001-E: Part labels + codes Vol III (Parts 11–13) | |
| 6 | CO-0001-F: Delete Category J (J-01–J-05) + all cross-refs | Every cross-ref → `*(see Supplementary Volume Supp. Part 4)*` before content deletion |
| 7 | CO-0001-G: Move BIO-01–BIO-05 from Part 8 to Appendix B | MOVE — update Part 8 intro "Supp-A" → "Appendix B" |
| 8 | CO-0001-H: Move TC-01–TC-05 from Part 8 to Appendix C | MOVE — update Part 8 intro "Supp-B" → "Appendix C" |
| 9 | CO-0001-I: Reposition Appendices as standalone `#` section | |
| 10 | CO-0001-J: Supp. Vol. Sections I–IV → Supp. Parts 1–4 | |
| 11 | CO-0001-K: Delete Supp. Vol. Section V (Revision Notes) | No redirect — content is on GitHub |
| 12 | CO-0001-L: Update front matter Part and Section Map | |
| 13 | Deferred: 82× "Chapter C" → "Part VIII §8.4" | ALL AMBIGUOUS at Stage 2 — present every instance to author; no batch execution |
| 14 | Deferred: 12× "Part VIII (case studies)" → "Part IX" (now Part 13) | |

Stage 6 gap register write after each pass. Update CO-0001 sign-off checklist on GitHub after completion.

### WS-1 Session B — Structural Verification

**`haiku-chunker` first (PI Rule 2 mandatory).** Document >11,000 lines post-changes. Section map from this run is the reference for all downstream sessions.

Parallel (Haiku 4.5):
- `cross-reference-resolver` — CO-0001 Cross-Reference Chase table (10 known + any new from Stage 3 reports)
- `guidebook-auditor` pass A — heading hierarchy; no orphaned Roman-numeral headings; no §III.x or §E.x or §V.x in Volumes I–III
- `volii-validator` — confirm V2-P8-XX universal; flag any remaining V2-P4-XX
- `structure-auditor` — Appendices at correct `#` level; Supp. Parts 1–4 consistent hierarchy
- `markdown-formatter` — heading level inconsistencies from BIO/TC moves and Appendix repositioning

