## Part 13 — Commit Convention and Session Discipline

**Commit messages:** `{skill-name}: {action} [{YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM}]`

**Checkpoint format (1–2 lines max):**
```
CHECKPOINT [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM] — task: {task} — stage: {stage} — status: {done/in-progress/blocked}
```

**Session end:** Always invoke `session-consolidator`. Never drop state. PUT fails → output YAML as fenced code block; instruct manual paste.

**Context limit approaching:** Complete current stage. Do not start a new one. Invoke `session-consolidator`. Instruct new chat with handoff summary.

**Suggested session-level commit milestones:**
- `fix-linebreaks: full source file conversion prep [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM]`
- `find-and-replace: CO-0001-A through CO-0001-L execution [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM]`
- `cross-reference-resolver: CO-0001 chase complete [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM]`
- `find-and-replace: tier renumber GAP-066 execution [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM]`
- `item-specification-writer: DBL thin-base + Protactile integration [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM]`
- `item-specification-writer: DBL room matrix pass complete [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM]`
- `research-log-manager: BPC corrections batch complete [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM]`
- `bibliography: v9.0 master bibliography committed [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM]`
- `chunk-assembler: v9.0 draft assembled [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM]`
- `session-consolidator: v9.0 session close [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM]`
